Prince Misuzulu Zulu KWANONGOMA - Prince Misuzulu Zulu has been named as the preferred new AmaZulu King. AmaZulu Queen Regent Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu's will was read out a while ago. She picked Misuzulu, her eldest son, to succeed King Goodwill Zwelithini.   Prince Misuzulu has been named as the preferred new AmaZulu King. AmaZulu Queen Regent Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu's will was read out a while ago. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/CMxLXD7CZk WATCH: Prince Misuzulu enters with Amabutho The king passed away earlier this year and the late Queen Regent passed away last week. The Queen's will was read out by her lawyer, Advocate Madoda Madonsela. READ: Buthelezi: Queen's will to be read at 5pm The queen's body was interred in KwaNongoma in the early hours of the morning. Family, friends and dignitaries then paid their respects at a memorial service at the palace. The Queen was fondly remembered for helping others and teaching villagers new skills. AmaZulu Queen Regent Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu picked Misuzulu, her eldest son, to succeed King Goodwill Zwelithini. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/aiWgzlX5hW AmaZulu Queen Regent Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu picked Misuzulu, her eldest son, to succeed King Goodwill Zwelithini. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/aiWgzlX5hW Celebrations at the royal palace after Prince Misuzulu was named as the preferred new AmaZulu King. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/q3JmogDDi2